, Action, Thing!\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|11|24}}\n| ShortSummary        = \n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 25\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 25\n| Title               = The Thing and the Captain's Ghost\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|12|1}}\n| ShortSummary        = The Yancy Street Gang dares Ben and his friends to stay on a haunted ship for a night.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 26\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 26\n| Title               = The Thing and the Absent-Minded Inventor\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|12|1}}\n| ShortSummary        = \n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n|}\n\n==The New Fred and Barney Show==\nThe \"Fred and Barney\" half of the show consisted of a second season of seven new 30-minute episodes of ''[[The New Fred and Barney Show]]'' combined with reruns of first-season episodes.\n\n===Episodes===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#FFFFFF\"\n! style=\"background:#FF681F; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|N\u00ba|Number}}\n! style=\"background:#FF681F; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|Ep|Episode}}\n! style=\"background:#FF681F\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#FF681F; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 11\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 1\n| Title               = Stone Age Werewolf\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|9|8}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred and Barney go on a fishing trip to an island rumoured to be haunted by a werewolf, but once they arrive, bad weather forces them to stay in the cabin of a friendly old man who is also the island's only resident.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 12\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 2\n| Title               = Fred & Barney Meet the Frankenstsones\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|9|15}}\n| ShortSummary        = After Fred and Barney are loaded with household chores, Fred sees an ad for a new Condominium Spa and 